<h1 class="hero-h">Fractional CMO Los Angeles <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">— senior marketing leadership for B2B operators here.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Treetop works with B2B mid-market companies in Los Angeles and across California. If you're a founder or CEO between $3M and $30M ARR considering a fractional CMO, here's the Los Angeles-specific context and how to think about the engagement.</p>
<div class="tldr"><div class="tldr-l">Short answer</div><p class="tldr-p">Treetop offers fractional CMO services in Los Angeles, CA. Engagements run $8K-$25K/month for B2B mid-market companies needing senior marketing leadership without a full-time hire. Remote-first with quarterly in-person on-site for Los Angeles clients when scope warrants.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Why Los Angeles's B2B market is its own thing</h2>
<p class="body">LA's B2B ecosystem is bigger and more fragmented than people give it credit for. The market spans Westside SaaS, ad-tech in Santa Monica, fintech in Beverly Hills, healthcare tech in West LA, and a deep e-commerce/DTC infrastructure footprint. Most fractional CMO conversations here center around going from founder-led marketing to a scalable motion that doesn't require the CEO to write every email.</p>
<p class="body"><strong>Practical implications for marketing leadership:</strong></p>
<ul class="ul"><li>Strong founder + operator network, lots of capital, longer decision cycles than SF, expects polish.</li><li>Talent market for senior fractional operators is huge — meaning you have real options without paying SF/NY rates.</li><li>Most B2B buyers here want substance over hype. Marketing that survives in Los Angeles translates well to enterprise sales motion elsewhere.</li><li>Pipeline rhythm rewards consistency more than peaks — quarterly cadence beats one-off campaigns.</li></ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Treetop's Los Angeles engagement model</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Remote-first with quarterly on-site.</strong> Quarterly in-person leadership offsites for Los Angeles engagements where scope warrants. Otherwise structured remote cadence.</li>
<li><strong>1-2 days per week typical.</strong> Fractional means fractional — defined hours, not always-on.</li>
<li><strong>Builder profile.</strong> We ship work; we don't just present strategy decks.</li>
<li><strong>AI-fluent.</strong> Modern fractional CMO work compounds with AI workflows. We bring those — and we'll help you build them in-house.</li>
<li><strong>12-18 month engagements</strong> typical for compounding outcomes.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When to consider Treetop specifically</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li>You're a B2B founder/CEO at $3M-$30M ARR.</li>
<li>You're in Los Angeles or open to a remote-first engagement with quarterly on-site.</li>
<li>You want senior marketing leadership without a $300K+ full-time hire.</li>
<li>You want a fractional CMO who personally uses AI tooling, not just talks about it.</li>
<li>You can commit $8K-$25K/month for 12-18 months.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Verticals we work with in Los Angeles</h2>
<p class="body">B2B SaaS, fintech, entertainment tech, ad-tech, e-commerce platforms, healthcare tech.</p>
<p class="body">If your vertical isn't listed, the engagement model still applies. The framework (ICP → outbound → pipeline → ops) is vertical-agnostic; the specific tactics adapt.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you work with companies in Los Angeles?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes. Treetop works remotely with B2B mid-market clients in Los Angeles and across California. In-person quarterly on-site available for Los Angeles-based clients with scope to support it.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Are you based in Los Angeles?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Treetop is based in Austin, TX. We work with clients across the US remotely with in-person quarterly on-site when warranted.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">What's a typical fractional CMO engagement cost?</h3><p class="faq-qa">$8K-$25K/month depending on time commitment and scope. Typically 12-18 month engagements.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you offer fractional CRO services too?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes — fractional CRO engagements available for B2B companies whose sales/CS/RevOps alignment is broken.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How do I start an engagement?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Book the $1,500 AI Audit as a low-commitment first engagement, or schedule a call directly.</p></div>
</div></section>

